{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:psalms.62",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 62,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 62 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.62.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:1",
      "text": "Truly my soul waiteth upon God: from him cometh my salvation.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.62.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:2",
      "text": "He only is my rock and my salvation; he is my defence; I shall not be greatly moved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.62.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:3",
      "text": "How long will ye imagine mischief against a man? ye shall be slain all of you: as a bowing wall shall ye be, and as a tottering fence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.62.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:4",
      "text": "They only consult to cast him down from his excellency: they delight in lies: they bless with their mouth, but they curse inwardly. Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.62.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:5",
      "text": "My soul, wait thou only upon God; for my expectation is from him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.62.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:6",
      "text": "He only is my rock and my salvation: he is my defence; I shall not be moved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.62.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:7",
      "text": "In God is my salvation and my glory: the rock of my strength, and my refuge, is in God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.62.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:8",
      "text": "Trust in him at all times; ye people, pour out your heart before him: God is a refuge for us. Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.62.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:9",
      "text": "Surely men of low degree are vanity, and men of high degree are a lie: to be laid in the balance, they are altogether lighter than vanity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.62.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:10",
      "text": "Trust not in oppression, and become not vain in robbery: if riches increase, set not your heart upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.62.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:11",
      "text": "God hath spoken once; twice have I heard this; that power belongeth unto God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.62.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:12",
      "text": "Also unto thee, O Lord, belongeth mercy: for thou renderest to every man according to his work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
